# LabRat Docker Nginx

This is a simple static website project served with Nginx inside Docker.

## How to Build the Docker Image

1. Open a terminal in the project folder `labrat`.
2. Build the Docker image:

```bash
docker build -t labrat-nginx .
```

## How to Run the Container
```bash
docker run --name labrat-nginx -p 8080:80 labrat-nginx
```
The website will be accessible at: http://localhost:8080

##  How to Update the Website
> Make changes to your HTML, CSS, or other files inside the labrat folder.

Rebuild the Docker image:

```bash
docker build -t labrat-nginx .
```

### Stop and remove the old container (if running):

```bash
docker rm -f labrat-nginx
```

Start a new container with the updated image:

```bash
docker run --name labrat-nginx -p 8080:80 labrat-nginx
```

Now your updates are live! ðŸŽ‰